      "matched_primitive": null,
      "is_optional": false,
      "is_opaque": false,
      "is_external": false,
      "parallelizable": false,
      "conceptual_summary": "baseline_referenced_temporal_transition_detector. Computes local evidence of state change in a one-dimensional numeric sequence by comparing short-horizon behavior against a reference baseline and applying dual decision levels. A transition criterion marks candidate boundary segments, and an alarm criterion over a separate window confirms persistent activation to suppress transient fluctuations. The result is a timeline-aligned representation of detected transition onsets.. Applications: Structural health monitoring: detect initiation of damage-related regime shifts in vibration sequences relative to a quiescent baseline., Network engineering: detect start times of sustained traffic bursts in packet-rate streams using idle-state references., Neuroscience instrumentation: detect burst initiation in electrophysiological traces using rest-period calibrated thresholds., Industrial automation: detect onset of process faults in multistep production sensor channels by baseline-referenced transition gating.",
      "critic_notes": "",
      "decomposition_rationale": ""
